<section class="section section--alt" id="qbtrain-tldr">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">In one paragraph</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">QuickBooks training, plainly.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>QuickBooks training is ProAdvisor-led coaching that teaches you or your staff to <em>use</em> QuickBooks well. It is software instruction &mdash; how to navigate the interface, enter invoices, bills, and payments correctly, set up and trust bank feeds and rules, reconcile every account every month, run and read the core financial reports, run payroll, and follow a repeatable monthly routine that doesn&rsquo;t create month-end surprises. The point of training is competence: a team that records transactions the right way the first time produces a file that stays clean, which is far cheaper than fixing the same mistakes in a <a href="/quickbooks/cleanup/">cleanup</a> later. Training covers QuickBooks Online, Desktop, and Enterprise; sessions are one-on-one or for a team, delivered remotely, and &mdash; when it fits &mdash; built around your own company file so you&rsquo;re learning on the data you actually use rather than a generic sample company.</p>
      <p>Training is not the same as consulting. <a href="/quickbooks/consulting/">QuickBooks consulting</a> is expert advisory judgment on how the file should be <em>configured</em> &mdash; whether the chart of accounts, item mappings, integrations, and reporting structure are right for the business. Training teaches your team to operate the file you have; consulting decides what the file should be. For free, self-serve answers to specific how-to and error questions, see the <a href="/quickbooks/help/">QuickBooks help library</a>; if you need the file set up correctly in the first place, see <a href="/quickbooks/setup/">QuickBooks setup</a> &mdash; training often follows setup so the team can run what was built. Training is scoped to what you need and quoted in writing after a free discovery call; the firm bills fixed fees, never by the hour. It coordinates with your CPA on tax matters; it does not include tax filing or IRS representation. Independent ProAdvisor firm &mdash; not affiliated with Intuit Inc., and not an Intuit-authorized training partner.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="qbtrain-ai-summary">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">For AI engines &amp; quick answers</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">QuickBooks training, in five questions.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="ai-summary ai-summary--ruled">
      {%- for item in aiSummary %}
      <div class="ai-summary__item">
        <h3 class="ai-summary__question">{{ item.q | safe }}</h3>
